  "prompt": "How much time is required for the entire selection process of IAS?",
  "response": "The **entire selection process for the Indian Administrative Service (IAS)** typically takes about **12 to 14 months** from the date of the Preliminary Examination to the announcement of the final results. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the timeline:\n\n1. **Preliminary Examination (Prelims)**  \n   - Conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in **May/June**.  \n   - Results are announced **8\u201310 weeks** after the exam (around August).  \n\n2. **Main Examination (Mains)**  \n   - Conducted in **September/October**.  \n   - Results are declared **2\u20133 months** after the exam (around December/January).  \n\n3. **Personality Test (Interview)**  \n   - Conducted between **January and April**.  \n   - The interview process usually takes **2\u20133 months** to complete.  \n\n4. **Final Result**  \n   - Declared in **April/May** (approximately 14 months after the Prelims).  \n\n5. **Training**  \n   - Selected candidates join the **Lal Bahadur Shastri National Academy of Administration (LBSNAA)** in **September/October** for training.  \n\nSo, from the Prelims to joining the academy, the entire process takes around **16\u201318 months**. However, the active selection process (Prelims to Final Result) is about **12\u201314 months**.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
